article.headline: Chattanooga 58, Elon 45
article.story: CHATTANOOGA, Tenn. (AP) -- Nicchaeus Doaks and Khalil Hartwell scored 12 points each and Chattanooga had a 13-point free throw advantage in a 58-45 win Tuesday over Elon. Chattanooga (6-4, 3-0 Southern Conference) never trailed after a 32-32 tie early in the second half, but Elon (5-5, 3-1) got to within five points -- 48-43 -- with 6:18 left. Chattanooga then went on a 10-2 run. Ola Atoyebi led the Phoenix with 18 points and Montell Watson scored 10. Chattanooga made 15-of-29 free throws to 2-of-6 for the Phoenix. The Mocs led 28-23 at the half. Elon has not won away from home this season.
